<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTER ROLLER TYPE - Cleaning and Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Immerse all parts in clean solvent. Remove and dry.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Visually inspect all disassembled parts for nicks, burrs or scoring. If signs of damage are
                visible, replace the entire hydraulic cam follower.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>CHECK THE ROLLERS AS FOLLOWS:</para>
                    <seqlist style="arabic">
                        <item>
                            <para>WHILE PUSHING ON THE ROLLER IN NORMAL DIRECTION OF LOAD, EXAMINE FOR FREE ROTATION OF
                                ROLLER.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>VISUALLY INSPECT ROLLER FOR PITS OR ROUGHNESS.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>IF A ROLLER FAILS ANY ONE OF THE PRECEDING INSPECTION CRITERIA YOU MUST INSPECT THE
                                CAMSHAFT LOBES FOR DAMAGE.
                            </para>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4350406" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg5415" filename="../figcg5/CG5415.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.6 Hydraulic Valve Lifter Tester ZTSE-1893</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>THE ROLLER ON THE VALVE LIFTER IS NOT FLAT BUT ACTUALLY CROWNED BY DESIGN. THEREFORE A NORMAL
                        WEAR PATTERN WILL NOT TYPICALLY BE COMPLETELY ACROSS THE ROLLER.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
